# Part 2

# Summary of Changes
- Main Menu Loop: I changed the program so it doesn’t just end after one purchase. I added a while loop that keeps the system running, letting the user go back and forth between the store, their cart, and the history until they choose to "Exit".
- Managing the Cart: I added a new section where the user can actually manage what’s inside their cart. If they change their mind, they can remove a specific item or clear the whole cart. I also made sure that when an item is removed, the stock is automatically added back to the store inventory.
- Payment & Change: I improved the checkout process. Now, the system asks for a cash amount and checks if it's enough to cover the total. If it is, it automatically calculates the change; if not, it shows an error.
- Receipt & History: I used a Transaction array to keep track of every successful sale. Now, even after a checkout is done, I can go to the "History" menu to see a list of all past receipts, including the date and the final amount paid.
- Low Stock Alerts: To make the system smarter, I added a "scan" after every checkout. If any product has 5 or fewer items left in stock, a warning message pops up on the screen so the shop owner knows it's time to reorder.

# Key Features (Part 2)
- I reorganized the app into a persistent menu system. Instead of running once and closing, the program now stays open, allowing users to jump between the store, their cart, and the history log as needed.
- I updated the cart logic to be more flexible. Users can now view their current items, remove specific products, or clear the entire cart. I also built logic to ensure that if an item is removed, the stock is automatically returned to the store inventory.
- I implemented a "cashier" flow that calculates the grand total (including a 10% discount for orders over PHP 5000). The system validates cash input to ensure it covers the total and automatically calculates the change.
- To make the app more professional, I added a post-transaction scan. If a product's stock drops to 5 or below, the system flags it with a "Low Stock Alert" so the user knows what needs to be restocked.
- I created a system to store completed sales in an array. Users can now view a history of all past transactions, including receipt numbers and timestamps.
